1) Define a Java class person with private instance variables name and age. Provide four
constructors in the class, one with no arguments, second with name only as an argument,
third with age only as argument fourth with name & age as argument.

Code:

class Person {
    private String name;
    private int age;
    Person() {
        System.out.println("Default/non-parameterized constructor");
    }
    Person(String name) {
        System.out.println("only name as arg");
        this.name = name;
    }
    Person(int age) {
        System.out.println("only age as arg");
        this.age = age;
    }
    Person(String name,int age) {
        System.out.println("name and age as args");
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Person p1 = new Person();
        Person p2 = new Person(43);
        Person p3 = new Person("Jack");
        Person p4 = new Person("Jack",43);
        Person p5 = new Person(45);
    }
}

2) Define a class Employee with private instance variables empid, name and
salary. Create a static variable to store an integer value(initially 0),
which gets incremented on instantiation, this value can be use to generate emptied
so that every employee has autogenerated unique empid. Define a private method
to generate empid. Provide two constructors in the class, one is taking two arguments
(name and salary) and the other one is non parameterized. Non parameterized constructor
ask name and salary from the user.

Code:

public class Employee {
    private int empId;
    private String name;
    private float salary;
    static int var;
    Employee() {
        ++var;
        java.util.Scanner sr = new java.util.Scanner(System.in);
        this.generateEmpId();
        System.out.println("Enter name :");
        name = sr.next();
        System.out.println("Enter salary :");
        salary = sr.nextFloat();
    }
    Employee(String name, int salary) {
        ++var;
        this.generateEmpId();
        this.name = name;
        this.salary = salary;
    }
    private void generateEmpId() {
        this.empId = var;
    }
    void displayEmpDetails() {
        System.out.println("Employee ID : "+empId);
        System.out.println("Name        : "+name);
        System.out.println("Salary      : "+salary);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Employee e1 = new Employee();
        Employee e2 = new Employee("Jack",4300000);
        e1.displayEmpDetails();
        e2.displayEmpDetails();
    }
}

3) 
